(749, 16, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"9ce3b01\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"0ba4cc3\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d61b0a8\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"eael_dch_icon_new\":{\"value\":\"\",\"library\":\"\"},\"eael_dch_first_title\":\"Our\",\"eael_dch_last_title\":\"Speciality\",\"eael_dch_subtext\":\"<p><b>Life<\\/b>\\u00a0is a characteristic that distinguishes\\u00a0<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Physical body\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Physical_body\\\">physical entities<\\/a>\\u00a0that have\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Biological process\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biological_process\\\">biological processes<\\/a>, such as\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Cell signaling\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cell_signaling\\\">signaling<\\/a>\\u00a0and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Self-sustainability\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Self-sustainability\\\">self-sustaining<\\/a>\\u00a0processes, from those that do not, either because such functions have ceased (they have\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Death\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Death\\\">died<\\/a>), or because they never had such functions and are classified as inanimate. Various forms of life exist, such as\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Plant\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Plant\\\">plants<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Animal\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Animal\\\">animals<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Fungus\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Fungus\\\">fungi<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Protist\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Protist\\\">protists<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Archaea\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Archaea\\\">archaea<\\/a>, and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Bacteria\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Bacteria\\\">bacteria<\\/a>.\