(913, 170, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"9ce3b01\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"0ba4cc3\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d61b0a8\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"eael_dch_icon_new\":{\"value\":\"\",\"library\":\"\"},\"eael_dch_first_title\":\"Our\",\"eael_dch_last_title\":\"Speciality\",\"eael_dch_subtext\":\"<p><b>Life<\\/b>\\u00a0is a characteristic that distinguishes\\u00a0<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Physical body\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Physical_body\\\">physical entities<\\/a>\\u00a0that have\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Biological process\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biological_process\\\">biological processes<\\/a>, such as\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Cell signaling\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cell_signaling\\\">signaling<\\/a>\\u00a0and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Self-sustainability\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Self-sustainability\\\">self-sustaining<\\/a>\\u00a0processes, from those that do not, either because such functions have ceased (they have\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Death\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Death\\\">died<\\/a>), or because they never had such functions and are classified as inanimate. Various forms of life exist, such as\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Plant\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Plant\\\">plants<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Animal\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Animal\\\">animals<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Fungus\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Fungus\\\">fungi<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Protist\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Protist\\\">protists<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Archaea\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Archaea\\\">archaea<\\/a>, and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Bacteria\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Bacteria\\\">bacteria<\\/a>.\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Biology\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biology\\\">Biology<\\/a>\\u00a0is the science concerned with the study of life.<\\/p><p><span id=\\\"Definition\\\"><\\/span>There is currently no consensus regarding the definition of life. One popular definition is that\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Organism\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Organism\\\">organisms<\\/a>\\u00a0are\\u00a0<a class=\\\"mw-redirect\\\" title=\\\"Open system (thermodynamics)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Open_system_(thermodynamics)\\\">open systems<\\/a>\\u00a0that maintain\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Homeostasis\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Homeostasis\\\">homeostasis<\\/a>, are composed of\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Cell (biology)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cell_(biology)\\\">cells<\\/a>, have a\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Biological life cycle\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Biological_life_cycle\\\">life cycle<\\/a>, undergo\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Metabolism\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Metabolism\\\">metabolism<\\/a>, can\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Cell growth\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Cell_growth\\\">grow<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Adaptation\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Adaptation\\\">adapt<\\/a>\\u00a0to their environment, respond to\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Stimulus (physiology)\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Stimulus_(physiology)\\\">stimuli<\\/a>,\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Reproduction\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Reproduction\\\">reproduce<\\/a>\\u00a0and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Evolution\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Evolution\\\">evolve<\\/a>. Other definitions sometimes include non-cellular life forms such as\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Virus\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Virus\\\">viruses<\\/a>\\u00a0and\\u00a0<a title=\\\"Viroid\\\" href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedi