(152, 1, '2020-08-05 15:54:24', '2020-08-05 15:54:24', '<h2>Our Speciality</h2>\n	   <p><b>Life</b>is a characteristic that distinguishes<a title=\"Physical body\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_body\">physical entities</a>that have<a title=\"Biological process\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biological_process\">biological processes</a>, such as<a title=\"Cell signaling\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_signaling\">signaling</a>and<a title=\"Self-sustainability\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Self-sustainability\">self-sustaining</a>processes, from those that do not, either because such functions have ceased (they have<a title=\"Death\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death\">died</a>), or because they never had such functions and are classified as inanimate. Various forms of life exist, such as<a title=\"Plant\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plant\">plants</a>,<a title=\"Animal\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal\">animals</a>,<a title=\"Fungus\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fungus\">fungi</a>,<a title=\"Protist\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Protist\">protists</a>,<a title=\"Archaea\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archaea\">archaea</a>, and<a title=\"Bacteria\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bacteria\">bacteria</a>.<a title=\"Biology\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology\">Biology</a>is the science concerned with the study of life.</p><p>There is currently no consensus regarding the definition of life. One popular definition is that<a title=\"Organism\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organism\">organisms</a>are<a title=\"Open system (thermodynamics)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open_system_(thermodynamics)\">open systems</a>that maintain<a title=\"Homeostasis\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homeostasis\">homeostasis</a>, are composed of<a title=\"Cell (biology)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_(biology)\">cells</a>, have a<a title=\